Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and low total CO₂, suggesting possible metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, supporting renal dysfunction and possible diabetic or metabolic decompensation. Liver enzymes and electrolytes are within normal limits. Findings are consistent with acute or chronic kidney disease, possibly with a metabolic component; clinical correlation and further nephrological evaluation are recommended.
